title: Central York grad Moyer a key piece to North Carolina's field hockey team
text:
Central York grad Moyer a key piece to North Carolina's field hockey team GameTimePA.com Posted: 10/17/2015 07:57:07 PM EDT Lauren Moyer and the Tar Heels have done plenty of celebrating this season. The team holds a 12-1 overall record and has outscored the competition 57-17 on the year. (Submitted) 
When the North Carolina field hockey team goes into action, Lauren Moyer has a job to do. And, it's not putting the ball in the net. 
Moyer, a former Central York standout, is playing midfield for the Tar Heels, who are ranked third in the country and sport a 12-1 overall record and a 4-1 mark in the Atlantic Coast Conference after a 2-1 victory over No. 4-ranked Duke on Friday.
